	//parental mail (2.0 feature)

	"Spam.Mom1": "Hey @, It's Robin again. How are things going on the farm?^I was trying out some new carpentry techniques and made this dresser. It's not my best work, but I figured you might want it! It felt like it'd be a waste to throw it out. Hopefully it's useful to you.",
	"Spam.Mom1Desc": "Robin Dresses You",

	"Spam.Mom2": "Greetings, @!^This is a notice to inform you that you have been given a gift enrollment in our esteemed Brews from Abroad program. How nice!^Periodically you'll receive a complimentary case of high-quality drinks from our beverage catalog, along with some notes about drinks themselves--ending in an activity kit you can use to create your own drinks! Enclosed is your first shipment:^^'Emerald Peaks' Single-Origin Green Tea^Tasting Notes: Light, Refreshing, Grassy^^This is a delightful blend of tea leaves grown and gathered in the mountainous areas east of the Calico Desert. This particular variety is well-liked for being a hardy, low-maintenance plant. If you're interested in growing your own, ask your local gardeners if they have any spare cuttings!^^This drink is best enjoyed in the early mornings before a hard day of work.",
	"Spam.Mom2Desc": "Brews From Abroad 1",

	"Spam.Mom3": "Brews From Abroad: Shipment 3^^'Sunrise' Golden Ginger Ale^Tasting Notes:Zesty, Peppery, Bright^^This drink is made with fresh Gotoran ginger. This particular batch has been crafted with yuzu citrus for an especially zesty punch!^While commonly used as a remedy for nausea, it's also great when enjoyed anytime you're feeling a little lucky or want to spice things up.",
	"Spam.Mom3Desc": "Brews From Abroad 3",

	"Spam.Mom4": "What do you get someone who has everything? I dunno, but most people seem to say 'gambling with someone else's cash.'^Enjoy!^^(This message has been paid for by the Ferngill Lottery.)",
	"Spam.Mom4Desc": "Let's Go Gambling?",

	"Spam.Dad1": "Hey, @!^It's Robin. I forgot to drop this off earlier. The old phone in your grandpa's house was too beat up to use, so I figured I'd give you one of the spares I had lying around.^Call me if you need anything, okay? Good luck getting the old place running again!",
	"Spam.Dad1Desc": "Robin Phones You",

	"Spam.Dad2": "Brews From Abroad: Shipment 2^^'Cafe Obsidian' Premium Blend Espresso^Tasting Notes: Chocolatey, Fruity, Smooth^^Today's package features the finest coffee from Cafe Obsidian, a small-batch coffee roaster located in the Gem Sea. After growing their coffee beans on fertile volcanic soil, artisans carefully roast and craft their coffee into a strong, easy-to-use liquid concentrate.^^Easily take it anywhere on your travels, just add fresh water whenever you're ready for a taste of the islands.",
	"Spam.Dad2Desc": "Brews From Abroad 2",

	"Spam.Dad3": "Today marks your final package from the Brews From Abroad program. We hope you enjoyed our beverages, but our last gift will allow you to keep enjoying flavors from around the world!^Enclosed is our Brew-It-Yourself kit containing everything you need to create your own drinks.^Contents:^6x Brew-It-Yourself Flatpack Kegs^1x Keg Assembly Manual and Tool Set^1xBrewing Yeast Sampler Pack^1xBeginner's Brewing Tips and Tricks Book",
	"Spam.Dad3Desc": "Brew It Yourself",

	"Spam.Dad4": "Nice work, kid.^You've made over a hundred grand in the time you've been here. One of these days you'll be a millionaire, I just know it. Here's a little something special from me to you.^Keep it up.",
	"Spam.Dad4Desc": "The Gift of the Century",

